My ticket number was finally out, I got up, draped in my dignity, and then I wondered: do we really know why they leave, these people?
Those who do not flee a war.
Are they really better at home?
So I looked for a country whose inhabitants would flee en masse and that would not be at war.
It was not very difficult, the International Organization for Migration had just released a report, and the country whose largest number of nationals in absolute terms had attempted to cross the Mediterranean between January and March 2015, it was the Gambia.
